<font color="#FF0000">HOW SHOULD THE VNW BE TREATED.</font><br>
<tt>Wed Mar 26  9:58:54 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I want to emphasis the importance of dispelling<br>
the image of all VETS as druggies. At the same<br>
time we need to dispell the image of all anti-<br>
war protesters being HIPPIES. <br><br>
Bring in Vets to speak in schools, bring in anti-war<br>
protesters to speak. Know that their is a range<br>
of Vets from those who still think the war was right<br>
to those who now do not. Know that people were<br>
opposed to the war for pacifist reasons, economic<br>
reasons and anti-imperialist reasons.<br><br>
The answer is to present the many facets of the <br>
war and students need to understand that it is<br>
not black and white, but grey with many shadings<br>
to all of the issues.<br><br>
Don't we all wish it was black and white. That would<br>
make our lives so much easier. 
<p><code>-- jproujan@k12s.phast.umass.edu  (Jed Proujansky) </code><p>


